  • applications : Application Operations

    • Show/Hide
    • List Operations
    • Expand Operations
    • Raw

      • get /v2/servers/{serverName}/vhosts/{vhostName}/applications

        • Retrieves the list of Applications for the specifed vhost

        Implementation Notes

        This API is available in builds 15089 or later.

        Response Class

        • Model
        • Model Schema
        ApplicationsConfig {
        serverName (string),
        saveFieldList (array[string], optional),
        version (string),
        applications (array[AppShortObject])
        }
        AppShortObject {
        drmEnabled (boolean),
        streamTargetsEnabled (boolean),
        appType (string),
        transcoderEnabled (boolean),
        dvrEnabled (boolean),
        id (string),
        href (string)
        } 
        {
  "serverName": "",
  "saveFieldList": [
    ""
  ],
  "version": "",
  "applications": [
    {
      "drmEnabled": false,
      "streamTargetsEnabled": false,
      "appType": "",
      "transcoderEnabled": false,
      "dvrEnabled": false,
      "id": "",
      "href": ""
    }
  ]
}


        Parameters

        Parameter Value Description Parameter Type Data Type
        serverName Reserved for future use path string
        vhostName path string

        Response Messages

        HTTP Status Code Reason Response Model
        200 Ok
        400 Bad Request
        402 Payment Required
        404 Not Found
        415 Unsupported Media Type
        Hide Response

        Request URL

        http://localhost:8087/v2/servers/_defaultServer_/vhosts/_defaultVHost_/applications

        Response Body

        <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><error><wowzaServer>4.8.0</wowzaServer><code>403</code><message>Your IP address (172.17.0.1) has been blocked</message></error>

        Response Code

        403

        Response Headers

        {
          "Content-Type": "text/xml; charset=UTF-8",
          "Date": "Tue, 08 Sep 2020 05:24:30 GMT",
          "Server": "Restlet-Framework/2.2.2"
        }

      • post /v2/servers/{serverName}/vhosts/{vhostName}/applications

        • Adds an Application to the list of Applications for the specifed vhost

        Implementation Notes

        This API is available in builds 15089 or later.

        Parameters

        Parameter Value Description Parameter Type Data Type
        serverName Reserved for future use path string
        vhostName path string
        body
        		body
        • Model
        • Model Schema
        ApplicationConfig {
        httpOptimizeFileReads (boolean),
        captionLiveIngestType (string),
        streamConfig (StreamConfigurationConfig),
        serverName (string),
        description (string),
        webRTCConfig (WebRTCConfig),
        mediaCacheSourceList (array[string]),
        repeaterOriginURL (string),
        clientStreamReadAccess (string),
        appType (string): ,
        pingTimeout (integer),
        vodTimedTextProviders (array[string]),
        saveFieldList (array[string], optional),

        }
        StreamConfigurationConfig {
        streamType (string),
        storageDirExists (boolean),
        keyDir (string),
        createStorageDir (boolean),
        liveStreamPacketizer (array[string]),
        serverName (string),
        storageDir (string),
        saveFieldList (array[string], optional),

        }

        templates (array[ShortObject]),
        serverName (string),
        saveFieldList (array[string], optional),
        version (string)
        }
        ShortObject {
        id (string),
        href (string)
        }

        filename (string),
        serverName (string),
        saveFieldList (array[string], optional),
        version (string),
        verimatrixStreamMaps (array[VerimatrixStreamMapsConfig$VerimatrixStreamMapConfig])
        }

        buyDRMStreamNameMapFile (string),

      • post /v2/servers/{serverName}/vhosts/{vhostName}/applications/{appName}

        • Adds the specified Application configuration

      • put /v2/servers/{serverName}/vhosts/{vhostName}/applications/{appName}/instances/{instanceName}/dvrstores/actions/{action}

        Implementation Notes

        This API is available in builds 15942 or later.

        Parameters

        Parameter Value Description Parameter Type Data Type
        serverName Reserved for future use path string
        action The action which should be performed by the server path string
        dvrConverterDefaultFileDestination The file location to use when converting a nDVR store, the default is configured as the StorageDir in the application in use query string
        dvrConverterDebugConversions Indicates if the conversion should have debugging enabled, can be true or false, default is false query string
        dvrConverterContinueOnSourceErrors Indicates if the conversion should continue even if errors are detected, can be true or false, default is true query string
        dvrConverterAudioVideoSyncEnable Indicates if the audio/video offset should be detected and conversion only started after the sync in no longer detected or over default allowable time. Can be true or false, default is false query string
        dvrConverterAudioVideoMaxOffset Indicates the maximum audio/video timecodes can be out of sync query string
        dvrConverterAudioVideoMaxBuffer Indicates the maximum time a correct audio/video sync will be searched for before giving up query string
        dvrConverterStartTime A start time in UTC from where the conversion should start in the store, default is the first entry in the store query string
        dvrConverterEndTime A end time in UTC where the conversion should end in the store, default is to the end of the store query string
        dvrConverterDuration A duration for the conversion either added to the start or subtracted from the end time, if you use duration you can not use start and end query string
        dvrConverterOutputFilename Indicates the output filename if not using the default, which is the name of the store being converted query string
        dvrConverterStoreList The comma-separated list of stores to convert query string
        vhostName The name of the current VHost the action will be performed on path string
        appName The application name needed for this REST call path string
        instanceName The application instance name needed for this REST call path string

        Response Messages

        HTTP Status Code Reason Response Model
        200 Ok
        400 Bad Request
        402 Payment Required
        404 Not Found
        415 Unsupported Media Type
        Hide Response

        Request URL

        Response Body

        Response Code

        Response Headers

      • get /v2/servers/{serverName}/logfiles/{logName}

        • Retrieves the contents of a Server Log with the specified log name

        Implementation Notes

        This API is available in builds 15089 or later.

        Response Class

        • Model
        • Model Schema
        ServerLogFileConfig {
        endOffset (integer),
        logStartDate (string),
        logDate (string),
        endDate (string),
        serverName (string),
        version (string),
        logLines (array[string]),
        filterStr (string),
        retLineCount (integer),
        logFields (string),
        logSoftware (string),
        startOffset (integer),
        searchStr (string),
        regexSearch (boolean),
        logVersion (string),
        saveFieldList (array[string], optional),
        fileLength (integer),
        startDate (string)
        } 
        {
  "endOffset": 0,
  "logStartDate": "",
  "logDate": "",
  "endDate": "",
  "serverName": "",
  "version": "",
  "logLines": [
    ""
  ],
  "filterStr": "",
  "retLineCount": 0,
  "logFields": "",
  "logSoftware": "",
  "startOffset": 0,
  "searchStr": "",
  "regexSearch": false,
  "logVersion": "",
  "saveFieldList": [
    ""
  ],
  "fileLength": 0,
  "startDate": ""
}


        Parameters

        Parameter Value Description Parameter Type Data Type
        serverName Reserved for future use path string
        lineCount The number of log lines requested, where a postive number indicates log lines after startOffset and a negative number indicate log lines before startOffset query string
        startOffset The byte offset in the file at which to begin getting log lines query string
        filter A string containing a list of predefined search filters separated by | where valid strings are noDebug,noInfo,noWarn,noError,noHeader,noColumnHeadings query string
        search A string containing a literal string on which to filter or a regex query string
        regexSearch Indicates if the 'search' parameter is a regex or a literal string query string
        head Returns the first x lines from the requested log file, the overrides the startoffset and linecount values query string
        tail Returns the last x lines from the requested log file, the overrides the startoffset and linecount values query string
        logName The name of the log path string

        Response Messages

        HTTP Status Code Reason Response Model
        200 Ok
        400 Bad Request
        402 Payment Required
        404 Not Found
        415 Unsupported Media Type
        Hide Response

        Request URL

        Response Body

        Response Code

        Response Headers

        lineCount The number of log lines requested, where a postive number indicates log lines after startOffset and a negative number indicate log lines before startOffset query string
        startOffset The byte offset in the file at which to begin getting log lines query string
        filter A string containing a list of predefined search filters separated by | where valid strings are noDebug,noInfo,noWarn,noError,noHeader,noColumnHeadings query string
        search A string containing a literal string on which to filter or a regex query string
        regexSearch Indicates if the 'search' parameter is a regex or a literal string query string
        head Returns the first x lines from the requested log file, the overrides the startoffset and linecount values query string
        tail Returns the last x lines from the requested log file, the overrides the startoffset and linecount values query string
        startDate The start date to filter on (UTC milliseconds) query string
        endDate The end date to filter on (UTC milliseconds) query string
        logType The type of the log path string

        Response Messages

        HTTP Status Code Reason Response Model
        200 Ok
        400 Bad Request
        402 Payment Required
        404 Not Found
        415 Unsupported Media Type
        Hide Response

        Request URL

        Response Body

        Response Code

        Response Headers
